member.example:
This sample shows how to call SpreadModelAsync with required request content.

var credential = new AzureKeyCredential("<key>");
var client = new SpreadClient(credential);

var data = new {
    name = "<name>",
    age = 1234,
};

Response response = await client.SpreadModelAsync(RequestContent.Create(data));
Console.WriteLine(response.Status);

member.remarks:
Below is the JSON schema for the request payload.
Request Body:
Schema for Thing: { name: string, # Required. age: number, # Required. }

